---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Access — The Space Between"
  description="Full access statement for The Space Between events in Burton upon Trent, including step-free access, BSL, quiet spaces, access fund, and how to tell us what you need."
>
  <main id="main">

    <!-- ── Page hero ────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="page-hero">
      <div class="container page-hero__inner">
        <a href="/#access" class="page-hero__back">
          <span aria-hidden="true">←</span> Back to the site
        </a>
        <h1 class="page-hero__title">Access</h1>
        <p class="page-hero__sub">
          The Space Between is for everyone in Burton. Here's exactly what
          we're doing to make that true, and how to tell us if we can do more.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ── Content ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────── -->
    <div class="page-content">
      <div class="container page-content__inner">

        <div class="prose">

          <h2>Step-free access</h2>
          <p>
            All main venues used by The Space Between have step-free entry:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Burton Library — step-free entry via main doors; lift to upper floors</li>
            <li>The Brewhouse Arts Centre — step-free entry and accessible toilets throughout</li>
            <li>Stapenhill Gardens — fully accessible outdoor space</li>
            <li>Burton Market Place — open public space, step-free</li>
            <li>Multiple venues (Love Your Local, Community Music Trail) — access details listed with each individual venue</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            If you're unsure about a specific venue, email us before the event and we'll confirm
            exactly what to expect when you arrive.
          </p>

          <h2>Quiet spaces</h2>
          <p>
            A calm, low-stimulus space is available at most indoor events. It's not signposted
            as a medical space — it's just a quiet room where you can take a breath and come
            back in when you're ready. Ask any steward when you arrive and they'll show you
            where it is.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you need to know in advance whether a quiet space will be available at a
            specific event, contact us and we'll confirm.
          </p>

          <h2>BSL interpretation</h2>
          <p>
            British Sign Language interpretation is available at any event. Give us at least
            five working days' notice and we'll arrange a qualified interpreter. There's no
            charge for this.
          </p>
          <p>
            Email <a href="mailto:accessibility@sonicboom.org.uk?subject=BSL%20request%20%E2%80%94%20The%20Space%20Between">accessibility@sonicboom.org.uk</a> with
            the event name and date.
          </p>

          <h2>Access fund</h2>
          <p>
            If the cost of a ticketed event is a barrier to attending, get in touch. We have
            a small access fund and will do what we can. We won't ask you to explain why —
            just tell us which event you'd like to come to.
          </p>
          <p>
            Email <a href="mailto:accessibility@sonicboom.org.uk?subject=Access%20fund%20%E2%80%94%20The%20Space%20Between">accessibility@sonicboom.org.uk</a>.
          </p>

          <h2>Tickets for Good</h2>
          <p>
            Tickets for Good provides free and subsidised tickets to people facing poverty or
            financial hardship. Some of our ticketed events will be listed on their platform.
            Check the individual event page for whether Tickets for Good tickets are available,
            or visit <a href="https://ticketsforgood.co.uk/?utm_source=between&utm_medium=accessibility&utm_campaign=ticketsforgood" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">ticketsforgood.co.uk <span class="sr-only">(opens in new tab)</span></a>.
          </p>

          <h2>Sensory information</h2>
          <p>
            We aim to publish a short sensory guide for each event in advance — expected
            sound levels, lighting, whether there are sudden loud moments, whether strobe
            effects are used. These will be linked from each event page as they're confirmed.
            If you need specific information before that's available, ask us.
          </p>

          <h2>Safe Gigs for Women</h2>
          <p>
            The Space Between is a member of the Safe Gigs for Women scheme. All staff and
            volunteers are briefed on our zero-tolerance policy on harassment and unwanted
            contact. If something doesn't feel right at one of our events, please tell any
            member of staff, a steward, or the venue team. We will take it seriously.
          </p>

          <h2>Good Night Out</h2>
          <p>
            We're signed up to the Good Night Out campaign. Our staff and volunteers know
            what to do if someone reports harassment, and we work with venues who share the
            same commitment.
          </p>

          <h2>Tell us what you need</h2>
          <p>
            This page covers the things we've planned for. But we know that access needs
            are individual. If there's something not listed here that would make it possible
            for you to come to an event, email us and we'll see what we can do.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>
              <a href="mailto:accessibility@sonicboom.org.uk?subject=Access%20request%20%E2%80%94%20The%20Space%20Between">accessibility@sonicboom.org.uk</a>
            </strong>
          </p>
          <p>
            We aim to respond within two working days. For urgent requests in the days
            before an event, also try <a href="mailto:hello@sonicboom.org.uk?subject=Urgent%20access%20%E2%80%94%20The%20Space%20Between">hello@sonicboom.org.uk</a>.
          </p>

          <h2>Website accessibility</h2>
          <p>
            This website aims to meet WCAG 2.2 Level AA. If you find something that doesn't
            work with your assistive technology, or anything that makes the site harder to use,
            please tell us at <a href="mailto:accessibility@sonicboom.org.uk?subject=Website%20access%20%E2%80%94%20The%20Space%20Between">accessibility@sonicboom.org.uk</a>
            and we'll fix it.
          </p>
          <p>
            We use Cloudflare Web Analytics, which does not use cookies or track personal
            data. There is no cookie banner on this site.
          </p>

        </div>

        <div class="page-back">
          <a href="/#access" class="btn btn-ghost-dark">
            <span aria-hidden="true">←</span> Back to the site
          </a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ── Page hero ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .page-hero {
    background: var(--ink);
    padding-block: clamp(var(--space-10), 8vw, var(--space-16));
    border-bottom: 3px solid var(--ember);
  }

  .page-hero__inner {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-5);
  }

  .page-hero__back {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--body);
    text-decoration: none;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.4em;
    transition: color 150ms var(--ease-out);
    width: fit-content;
  }
  .page-hero__back:hover { color: var(--paper); }
  .page-hero__back:focus-visible {
    outline: 3px solid var(--ember);
    outline-offset: 4px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  .page-hero__title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 7vw, 4.5rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    font-optical-sizing: auto;
    color: var(--paper);
    line-height: 1.0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .page-hero__sub {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.2rem);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--body);
    max-width: 56ch;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Content ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .page-content {
    background: var(--paper);
    padding-block: clamp(var(--space-10), 8vw, var(--space-16));
  }

  .page-content__inner {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-12);
  }

  /* ── Prose ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .prose {
    max-width: 68ch;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
  }

  .prose h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 3vw, 1.75rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: -0.015em;
    font-optical-sizing: auto;
    color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.2;
    margin: var(--space-10) 0 var(--space-4);
  }
  .prose h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }

  .prose p {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: clamp(0.95rem, 2vw, 1.05rem);
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .prose ul {
    padding-left: var(--space-5);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }
  .prose li {
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: clamp(0.95rem, 2vw, 1.05rem);
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .prose a {
    color: var(--red);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  .prose a:hover { color: var(--ink); }
  .prose a:focus-visible {
    outline: 3px solid var(--ember);
    outline-offset: 3px;
    border-radius: 2px;
  }

  .prose strong { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 700; }

  /* ── Back link ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .page-back {
    padding-top: var(--space-6);
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(26, 18, 18, 0.1);
  }
</style>
